MULTICON
--------

Allows you to get correct colors icons with MultiTOS and a graphic card,
tested on TT.

To correct the icons colors
---------------------------
What you need:

C:\DESKCICN.RSC file with color icons that are loaded by the system.
	The name of the first icon must be SSSSTTTTAAAA
	The name of the very last icon must be EEEENNNNDDDD

If you have TT RAM, then this file is loaded in TT RAM, so the flags of
MULTICON.PRG must be set to run from TT RAM.

path\MULTICON.PRG that must be installed as auto run file.
So, your NEWDESK.INF must contain the line:

#Z 01 path\MULTICON.PRG@

For example, I have saved the file in C:\MULTITOS, so my line is:

#Z 01 C:\MULTITOS\MULTICON.PRG@

If you want a background...
---------------------------

	You must have TGA 16 bits uncompressed images for every
resolution. The name of the file gives the resolution:
	08000600.TGA for 800x600.
	Always eight digits for xxxxyyyy.TGA.
	The images are located in the same folder as MULTICON.

	To get the image as a background, the desktop setting must be:
	- white color
	- one of the 6 intermediate patterns

	So your NEWDESK.INF file must contain a line:

#Q .. .. .. .. 10 ..
	The fifth number indicates the pattern (1) and the color (0
	white).

	If you want to go back to a simple background, just modify the
settings, if you want a white background, just select the empty (0) or
solid (7) pattern.

If you want a sound at start...
-------------------------------
	You must have a file named MULTICON.SND with raw data:
	- mono sound, 8 bits signed, 12.5KHz.
	Always in the same folder!

That's all !

Should run on every graphic card with 15-16-24 or 32 bits colors.

At start, the desktop is displayed for a few seconds with bad icons, then
the patch is applied.
And after some more seconds, the colors are correct!

